1. Download remote debugger  with respect to VS version and installed in the local machine.
2. Related files will be Located at the below location
C:\Program Files\Microsoft Visual Studio 14.0\Common7\IDE\Remote Debugger\x64
3. Go to Remote machine and copy the Remote Debugger folder in any location.
4.Run the msvsmon.exe application as Administrator from the below link in the remote computer
5. Goto Tools/Options of the VS debugger (msvsmon.exe) and set the 'No Authentication option with allow all users'
6. Copy the Dll and its PDB files in the remote computer.
7. Start the application in the remote machine
8. In local machine (VS) attached the debugger by selecting the remote machine and running application(EXE which responsible to load the the corresponding DLL)
9. Attach the deubbger from the local machine and check the symbols are loaded or not.(Press Ctrl+Alt+U)




NOTE: Install the VS 2022 debugger and folders from "C:\Program Files\Microsoft Visual Studio 17.0\Common7\ide\Remote Debugger"
